FT  22 JAN 94 / London Stock Exchange: TV stocks active on ruling
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, JOEL KIBAZO, STEVE THOMPSON and CLARE GASCOIGNE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The predatory television stocks, Granada and Carlton Communications, rallied
on the news that their respective bids would not be referred to the MMC
providing certain undertakings were met. The afternoon announcement caused
some confusion, with Carlton's shares - already marked down on the day
through profit-taking - dipping to 986 at one point before the company said
it had already indicated its willingness to give such undertakings. Shares
recovered to finish down 12 at 1006p, while Granada moved up 16 to 591p. LWT
were up 11 to 699p and Central down 50 to 3065p.
Elsewhere profit-taking knocked Reuters back 27 to 1897p and EMAP lost 9 to
close at 465p. Reed and Pearson were slightly stronger on the day, closing
at 902p, up 6, and 640p, up 6, respectively.
