<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JAN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Nutmeg and mace prices were firm this week with only limited offers emerging
from Indonesia, reports Man Producten. Spot Europe prices were USDollars
1,550 a tonne for bwp and Dollars 1,700 for shrivels and Dollars 1,800 for
abcds. The spot price for mace was Dollars 3,000 a tonne, with shipments at
higher levels. Grenadan nutmegs increased their cif prices: guns were at
Dollars 1,400 a tonne and suns Dollars 1,900 for February shipment, while
mace No. 2 was offered at Dollars 2,650 a tonne for shipment only after
April. Indonesian cassia prices were unchanged with ka/va sticks at Dollars
2,300 a tonne, spot and Dollars 2,150, shipment, and kb br/cl at Dollars
1,600 spot, Dollars 1,475, shipment, with discounting on later shipments.
Madagascan cinnamon was offered at FFr5.70 a kg, with Seychelles at Dollars
1,400 a tonne, cif.
