<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 94 / International Company News: Japanese insurer in UK venture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMIKO TERAZONO
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Sanshin, a Japanese non-life insurance company affiliated with Sanwa Bank, a
leading commercial bank, is to set up a joint reinsurance venture in the UK
with Robert Fleming Insurance Brokers, part of the UK merchant bank group.
Sanshin Fleming Reinsurance Brokers will be established in London this
month, with Sanshin and Robert Fleming Insurance each holding 42.5 per cent
stakes, and Japan England Insurance Brokers the remaining 15 per cent.
The company will be the first Japanese insurance company to be involved in
the reinsurance business.
