<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Aim shares lose 15p as profits dive
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax profits at Aim Group, the maker of aircraft interior fittings, fell
58 per cent in the six months to October 31. And the second half is expected
to be hit by the delay in a large contract.
The shares lost 15p to 150p. When the company warned of the difficulties
with a Saab contract in November, the shares fell 30p to 143p.
On turnover 24 per cent lower at Pounds 15.5m (Pounds 20.4m), including
Pounds 152,000 (Pounds 950,000) from property development, pre-tax profits
were Pounds 1.18m (Pounds 2.82m). The comparable figure included Pounds
1.34m from profit on disposal of subsidiaries.
Earnings per share were 5.4p (15.9p) and the interim dividend is maintained
at 1.5p.
