FT  21 JAN 94 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain's ice skating stars Torvill and Dean are in an almost impossible
position at the European Figure Skating Championships in Copenhagen which
are covered in Ice Skating (8.00 BBC1). There will be disappointment not
only if they fail to win but if they fail to repeat that clean-sweep of
sixes which they achieved with their 'Mack And Mabel' number at the same
venue in 1982. Today is the first time their new free dance routine will be
tested internationally.
There are several ways of dealing with nuisance phone callers. If you have
the chutzpah you can outdo them at their own game. Keeping a referee's
whistle by the phone and blowing it hard can also be effective. But our
favourite is to put the receiver down quietly on something soft and let the
nutters talk to themselves. Public Eye considers the problem (8.00 BBC2).
Further Abroad is a series that viewers either love or loathe. Jonathan
Meades is a presenter whose idiosyn-cratic style and attitudes I enjoy, but
cause some critics to howl in rage. Today he looks at golf courses (9.30
BBC2).
