<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 94 / Labour health motion defeated
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Labour party last night lost a motion in the Commons attacking
bureaucratic growth in the National Health Service 'at the expense of
patient care'.
The vote was lost by 311 votes to 265, a government majority of 46.
A government amendment welcoming 'the improvement in the efficiency of the
NHS which has resulted in a substantial increase in the number of patients
treated', was carried by 309 votes to 264, a government majority of 45.
</TEXT>
