<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 94 / Polly Peck inquiry man is charged
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN MASON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Michael Allcock, the Inland Revenue investigator who was involved in the
inquiry into Mr Asil Nadir, the former Polly Peck chairman, was yesterday
charged with two offences of conspiring to cheat the Inland Revenue, John
Mason writes.
Mr Allcock is charged with conspiring with Mr Hisham Alwan, a consultant
from Knightsbridge, London, and Mr David Shamoon, a company director from
Holland Park, London, to cheat the Revenue. Mr Alwan and Mr Shamoon were
both charged with one count each of conspiring with Mr Allcock.
Mr Allcock was suspended in September 1992 following an internal inquiry by
the Revenue into matters unconnected with Polly Peck. He was arrested in
July last year.
</TEXT>
